The paper deals with a network design problem on directed graphs, which involves finding an arborescence that maximizes a submodular function subject to a budget constraint. This problem is related to several areas in computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), graph theory (cs.GT), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and network economics (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
